race.description: Shamus Award At Rosemont Stud Maiden Plate
race.comment: SILENT ANSWER (8) debuted in a hot maiden at Cranbourne won by the smart Lyrics 'N' Song, battling away well there as a $5.50 chance. She looks suited rising in trip here with that experience under the belt and should prove hard to hold out. BOOMEROO (3) is a filly by Wootton Bassett on debut for the Freedman yard. She was an expensive yearling who draws well with Williams booked, wary. VENETIAN CHOICE (10) has run third in all three starts to date and should be suited rising in trip now given her breeding. She draws well and looks a key chance. STARTIN'SUMTHIN' (9) is a Ghaiyyath filly on debut who can run well.
